(6) Louisiana Council of Juvenile and Family Court Judges.
(7) Children's Code Committee of the Louisiana State Law Institute.
(8) Louisiana Department of Children and Family Services.
(9) Pelican Center for Children and Families.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force may seek input from other
relevant organizations or persons with knowledge or expertise, including but not limited to:
(1) Louisiana District Attorneys Association.
(2) Louisiana District Judge Association.
(3) Mental Health Advocacy Service.
(4) Southeast Louisiana Legal Services Corporation.
(5) Acadiana Legal Services Corporation.
(6) Office of the state public defender.
(7) Louisiana Court Appointed Special Advocates (CASA) Association.
(8) State child ombudsman.
(9) Current or former foster caregivers who have adopted a child out of foster care.
(10) Former foster youth.
(11) Former system-involved parents.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that each designating authority shall submit the
names of the designees and appointed members to the Louisiana Court Improvement
Program of the Louisiana Supreme Court no later than July 1, 2026.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana Court Improvement Program of
the Louisiana Supreme Court and Department of Children and Family Services shall provide
necessary staff to support the task force.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Louisiana Court Improvement Program of
the Louisiana Supreme Court and Department of Children and Family Services shall
communicate with all members and call meetings of the task force.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall adopt rules of procedure and
a meeting schedule, prepare an agenda for each meeting, and take any additional steps the
task force determines necessary to accomplish its goals, timely prepare its report, and make
its recommendations.
