BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene for its first meeting
no later than August 1, 2026, at the call of the Louisiana Court Improvement Program of the
Louisiana Supreme Court, and at the first meeting, the members shall elect officers as the
task force may deem appropriate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the task force shall constitute a
quorum for the transaction of business. All official actions of the task force shall require the
affirmative vote of a majority of the members.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
without compensation, except per diem or expenses reimbursement to which the member
may be individually entitled as a member of the respective organizations.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall report its findings and
propose recommendations, together with specific proposals for legislation, court rule
changes, professional training enhancement, and agency policy and practice reform by
written report to the Legislature of Louisiana and to the David R. Poynter Legislative
Research Library as required by R.S. 24:771 and 772, no later than February 1, 2027.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall terminate on the date of the
submission of its report or February 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to all
task force member organizations.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
